Package gw.api.exchangerates.test

Class FXExchangeRateSetSampleData

java.lang.Object
gw.api.exchangerates.test.FXExchangeRateSetSampleData
public final class FXExchangeRateSetSampleData extends Object
Utility class which facilitates loading/unloading sample data for FXExchangeRateSet and FXExchangeRate entities in the context of unit tests.

This class provides sample data context for specific test functions. Please refer to runWithSampleData functions for more information.

It also can be used to have sample data available for all tests within a unit test class.

Examples:

Example 1: Using lifecycle methods beforeClass and afterClass with default static sample data. 

 public class MyTest extends TestBase {
    private static final FXExchangeRateSetSampleData.Context SAMPLE_DATA_CONTEXT = new FXExchangeRateSetSampleData.Context();

   @Override
   protected void beforeClass() throws Exception {
      super.beforeClass();
      SAMPLE_DATA_CONTEXT.add(LOAD_STATIC_SAMPLE_DATA);
   }

   @Override
   protected void afterClass() throws Exception {
      SAMPLE_DATA_CONTEXT.destroy();
      super.afterClass();
   }

    public void testMethod() {
       // test code here
    }
 }

Example 2: Using lifecycle methods beforeMethod and afterMethod with default static sample data. 

 public class MyTest extends TestBase {
    private static final FXExchangeRateSetSampleData.Context SAMPLE_DATA_CONTEXT = new FXExchangeRateSetSampleData.Context();

    @Override
    protected void beforeMethod() throws Exception {
       super.beforeMethod();
       SAMPLE_DATA_CONTEXT.add(LOAD_TEST_SAMPLE_DATA);
    }

    @Override
    protected void afterMethod(Throwable possibleException) throws Exception {
      SAMPLE_DATA_CONTEXT.destroy();
      super.afterMethod(possibleException);
    }

    public void testMethod() {
       // test code here
    }
 }

Example 3: Using default static sample data within a block. 

 public class MyTest extends TestBase {

    public void testMethod() {
       FXExchangeRateSetSampleData.runWithSampleData(() -> {
          // test code here
          return null;
       });
    }
 }

    • runWithSampleData

      public static <T> T runWithSampleData(Supplier<T> supplier, Supplier<List<String>> loader)
      Execute a supplier after loading sample date. All registered sample data created will be removed after execution.

      Java Example: 

          runWithSampleData(() -> {
       // Unit test code here
       return null;
     }, () -> {
       Transaction.runWithNewBundle(bundle -> {
         // create and register all necessary instances for tests
         new FXExchangeRateSetBuilder().withPublicID("id:001").create(bundle);
         new FXExchangeRateSetBuilder().withPublicID("id:002").create(bundle);
       });
       return List.of("id:001", "id:002");
     });
      Type Parameters:
      T - type of the return, optional.
      Parameters:
      supplier - block containing business to be executed.
      loader - block containing the necessary code to load and register data that will be used then removed.
      Returns:
      any arbitrary value from the supplier.

    • createBuildersFromStaticTable

      public static List<FXExchangeRateSetBuilder> createBuildersFromStaticTable(List<Currency> baseCurrencies, List<FXRateMarket> markets, Date effectiveDate, Date expirationDate)
      Generates sample data for new exchange rate sets using information similar to that found in the deprecated gw.currency.fxrate.impl.FXRateServiceImpl class.

      This method creates instances of FXExchangeRateSetBuilder with the provided base currencies, markets, effective and expiration dates.

      If the list of base currencies is null, it uses all pre-set base currencies.

      If the list of markets is null, it uses all non-retired type codes.

      If the effective date is null, the current system date is used.

      Parameters:
      baseCurrencies - List of base currencies, or null to use all pre-set base currencies.
      markets - List of markets, or null to use all non-retired type codes.
      effectiveDate - Effective date for the exchange rate set, or null to use the current system date.
      expirationDate - Expiration date for the exchange rate set.
      Returns:
      A list of FXExchangeRateSetBuilder instances initialized with sample data.

    • createBuildersFromStaticTable

      public static List<ExchangeRateSetBuilder> createBuildersFromStaticTable(Date effectiveDate, Date expirationDate)
      Generates sample data for new exchange rate sets using information similar to that found in the deprecated gw.currency.fxrate.impl.FXRateServiceImpl class for the ExchangeRateSet entity.

      This method creates instances of ExchangeRateSetBuilder with the provided effective and expiration dates.

      If the effective date is null, the current system date is used.

      Parameters:
      effectiveDate - The effective date for the exchange rate set, or null to use the current system date.
      expirationDate - The expiration date for the exchange rate set.
      Returns:
      A list of ExchangeRateSetBuilder instances initialized with sample data.
